headline: EFX Q1 Earnings Call: Cloud Investments Drive Product Launches Amid Market Uncertainty
summary: Credit reporting giant Equifax (NYSE:EFX) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q1 CY2025, with sales up 3.8% year on year to $1.44 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $1.51 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.53 per share was 9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
